Czech Stocks Fall to Lowest Since March; Unipetrol, Erste Drop

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-06-08T13:24:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/czech-stocks-fall-to-lowest-since-march-unipetrol-erste-drop.html
The Czech Republic’s benchmark equity
index fell for a sixth day to a 2 1/2-month low as  Unipetrol AS (UNIP) ,
the country’s biggest oil refiner, and  Austria ’s  Erste Group
Bank AG (RBAG)  each fell more than 1.5 percent.  The PX gauge of 15 companies declined as much as 0.7
percent to 1,216.2, its lowest intraday level since March 18,
and was down 0.6 percent as of 3:23 p.m. in Prague. The index
headed for its longest stretch of declines in two years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  